The paper proposes a new graphical model for representing partial knowledge in a domain, which is relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The model also involves probabilistic reasoning, which is relevant to computational linguistics (cs.CL) and cryptography (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper discusses the dynamics of constructing the model, which could be relevant to social and information networks (cs.SI).
